Note something big here, though. An enchanter is a full class WITHOUT needing a charmed pet. An enchanter can do everything they need to without necessarily using a charmed pet, because most of the time, they're unreliable. If you're considering going up against that enchanter's perminently charmed pet Mage + pet vs Enchanter charmed pet, then yes, you might just win. Guess what, though? As I pointed out, if you're going up against an enchanter's charmed pet, the enchanter is standing RIGHT behind that pet, ready to use any and all tactics they know for crowd control to control YOU and your pet. <br>
<br>
So you focus on the charmed pet. Ok, you, 2-3-4 pets, most of a bar of mana, can take down that creature by itself. Now, you have to deal with the enchanter. Whups. You wasted all your mana dealing with their mob alone, now you have nothing left to work on the enchanter with (and they have a full bar of mana). This is, of course, considering that the enchanter LETS you have that much time to solo the charmed pet, and doesn't just take you down first by mezzing your pet, stunning you/pet, etc, etc, etc.<br>
<br>
